Sentencas: La0.1Sr0.9Co0.8Fe0.2O3-delta (LSCF1982) and La0.1Sr0.9Co0.8Fe0.2O3-delta-Ce0.9Gd0.1O2 (LSCF1982-GDC) composite oxygen electrodes with a GDC barrier layer are tested in yttria stabilized zirconia (YSZ) electrolyte-based reversible solid oxide cells (RSOCs).
Titulo: Performance of La0.1Sr0.9Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ and La0.1Sr0.9Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ-Ce0.9Gd0.1O2 oxygen electrodes with Ce0.9Gd0.1O2 barrier layer in reversible solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Three button cell assemblies (1: NiO-YSZ vertical bar YSZ/GDC vertical bar LSCF1982; 2: NiO-YSZ/NiO-YSZ vertical bar YSZ/GDC vertical bar LSCF1982; and 3: NiO-YSZ/NiO-YSZ vertical bar YSZ/GDC vertical bar LSCF1982-GDC) are fabricated and their performance in solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) and solid oxide electrolysis cell (SOEC) modes are studied at different temperatures (600 <= T/degrees C <= 800).
Titulo: Performance of La0.1Sr0.9Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ and La0.1Sr0.9Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ-Ce0.9Gd0.1O2 oxygen electrodes with Ce0.9Gd0.1O2 barrier layer in reversible solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The use of porous NiO-YSZ functional layer between hydrogen electrode and electrolyte leads to improvements in SOFC and SOEC (SOFC/SOEC) performance by improving the diffusion of reacting species inside the electrode.
Titulo: Performance of La0.1Sr0.9Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ and La0.1Sr0.9Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ-Ce0.9Gd0.1O2 oxygen electrodes with Ce0.9Gd0.1O2 barrier layer in reversible solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The effect of nature of oxygen electrode on SOFC/SOEC performance is studied, which indicates LSCF1982 oxygen electrode gives better performance than LSCF1982-GDC composite oxygen electrode, but LSCF1982-GDC composite oxygen electrode is more durable during reversible SOFC/SOEC operations.
Titulo: Performance of La0.1Sr0.9Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ and La0.1Sr0.9Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ-Ce0.9Gd0.1O2 oxygen electrodes with Ce0.9Gd0.1O2 barrier layer in reversible solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Stability of the button cells is studied in galvanostatic SOEC operation for 72 h and in reversible SOFC/SOEC operations.
Titulo: Performance of La0.1Sr0.9Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ and La0.1Sr0.9Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ-Ce0.9Gd0.1O2 oxygen electrodes with Ce0.9Gd0.1O2 barrier layer in reversible solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Current-voltage (I-V) tests and Electrochemical Impedance Spectroscopy (EIS) measurements indicate that the button cells show stable operation in SOEC mode.
Titulo: Performance of La0.1Sr0.9Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ and La0.1Sr0.9Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ-Ce0.9Gd0.1O2 oxygen electrodes with Ce0.9Gd0.1O2 barrier layer in reversible solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: But successive SOFC -> SOEC -> SOFC operations indicate that the cells are not completely reversible.
Titulo: Performance of La0.1Sr0.9Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ and La0.1Sr0.9Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ-Ce0.9Gd0.1O2 oxygen electrodes with Ce0.9Gd0.1O2 barrier layer in reversible solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The possible reason for poor reversibility is found to be related with the grain growth in LSCF1982-based oxygen electrodes.
Titulo: Performance of La0.1Sr0.9Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ and La0.1Sr0.9Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ-Ce0.9Gd0.1O2 oxygen electrodes with Ce0.9Gd0.1O2 barrier layer in reversible solid oxide fuel cells
